# Link Graveyard — Backend

Event-driven microservices backend for the Link Graveyard system.

## Architecture

- **NestJS API Gateway** (ackend-node/) — REST API, WebSockets, BullMQ queues, JWT auth
- **FastAPI Python Worker** (ackend-python/) — Playwright DOM scraping, OpenAI AI analysis, Celery tasks
- **PostgreSQL** — Primary relational database with JSONB support
- **Redis** — BullMQ message broker and Celery task queue

## Quick Start

### Prerequisites
- Docker & Docker Compose
- Node.js 20+
- Python 3.11+

### Environment Setup

`ash
cp .env.example .env
# Fill in OPENAI_API_KEY, JWT_SECRET, etc.
`

### Run with Docker Compose

`ash
docker-compose up --build
`

### Run NestJS Locally

`ash
cd backend-node
npm install
npx prisma migrate dev
npm run start:dev
`

### Run Python Worker Locally

`ash
cd backend-python
pip install -r requirements.txt
playwright install chromium
uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000
# In a separate terminal:
celery -A app.worker.tasks.celery_app worker --loglevel=info
`

## API Documentation

Swagger UI available at: http://localhost:3000/api/docs

## Key Endpoints

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| POST | /api/v1/auth/register | Register user |
| POST | /api/v1/auth/login | Login, receive JWT |
| POST | /api/v1/links | Submit link (202 Accepted) |
| GET | /api/v1/links | Get paginated inbox |
| PUT | /api/v1/links/:id/status | Update link status |
| GET | /api/v1/links/:id/why-did-i-save-this | Context reconstruction |
| GET | /metrics | Prometheus metrics |
| GET | /health (Python) | Health check |

## Testing

`ash
# NestJS
cd backend-node && npm run test:cov

# Python
cd backend-python && pytest -v
`
